Simulation Setting

\[A = {(x_1, x_2) | x_1^2 + x_2^2 \geq 10^2}\]

\[\beta_{1,x_1,x_2} = 10|sin(\frac{x_1}{2.5}) + cos(\frac{x_2}{2.5})|\] \[\beta_{2,x_1,x_2} = 5|sin(\frac{x_1}{3}) + cos(\frac{x_2}{3})|\]

\[\begin{align*} h(t,x_1,x_2) &= \beta_{1,x_1,x_2} \cdot C(t) + \beta_{2,x_1,x_2} \cdot C^{'}(t)\\ n(t) &= 1{onsets}\\ \end{align*}\]

For simulation, generate 100 timecourse data with AR(p) white noise. In this case, AR(1) model with \(\phi = 0.3\).

\[\begin{align*} Y(t,x_1,x_2) &= n(t) \cdot h(t,x_1,x_2) + \epsilon(t) & where\ \epsilon \sim AR(1)\\ \epsilon(t) &= \phi \cdot \epsilon(t-1) + \delta, & \delta \sim N(0,\sigma^2)\\ \end{align*}\]

0. Independent Model

\(Y_V = n \cdot h + \epsilon = X\beta_V + \epsilon\) where \(\epsilon \sim AR(1)\)

where \[\begin{align*} Y = \begin{pmatrix} Y(1)\\ Y(2)\\ \vdots \\ Y(T) \\ \end{pmatrix}, & X = \begin{pmatrix} C(1) & C^{'}(1)\\ \vdots \\ C(T) & C^{'}(T) \\ \end{pmatrix}, & \beta = \begin{pmatrix} \beta_1 \\ \beta_2 \end{pmatrix} \end{align*}\]

\(\hat{\beta_V} = (X^{'}\Sigma^{-1}X)^{-1}X^{'}\Sigma^{-1}Y_V\) where \[\begin{align*} \Sigma = Cov(\epsilon) = \frac{\sigma^2}{1-\phi^2}\begin{pmatrix} 1 & \phi & \phi^2 & \cdots & \phi^{T-1}\\ \phi & 1 & & \cdots & \phi^{T-2}\\ \vdots & & & \vdots\\ \phi^{T-1} & \cdots & & & 1\\ \end{pmatrix} \end{align*}\]

1. Gaussian Kernel Smoothing

\[\tilde{Y}(t,x_1,x_2) = \frac{\sum_i K(x_{1i}, x_{2i}| x_1, x_2, \sigma)Y(t,x_{1i}, x_{2i})}{\sum_i K(x_{1i}, x_{2i}| x_1, x_2, \sigma)}\]

\[\text{where } K(x_{1}, x_{2}| \mu_1, \mu_2, \sigma) = \frac{1}{2\pi\sigma^2}exp(-\frac{(x_1-\mu_1)^2 + (x_2-\mu_2)^2}{2\sigma^2})\]

\[\begin{align*} \tilde{Y}_V = \tilde{Y}(x_1,x_2) = \begin{pmatrix} \tilde{Y}(1,x_1,x_2)\\ \vdots \\ \tilde{Y}(T,x_1,x_2)\\ \end{pmatrix} \end{align*}\]

\[\hat{\tilde{\beta_V}} = (X^{'}\Sigma^{-1}X)^{-1}X^{'}\Sigma^{-1}\tilde{Y_V}\]

\[\begin{align*}\mathbb{E}(\hat{\tilde{\beta_V}}) &= \mathbb{E}((X^{'}\Sigma^{-1}X)^{-1}X^{'}\Sigma^{-1}\tilde{Y_V}) \\ &= (X^{'}\Sigma^{-1}X)^{-1}X^{'}\Sigma^{-1}\mathbb{E}\tilde{Y_V} \end{align*}\]

We know that \(\mathbb{E}(Y) = X\beta\).

\[\begin{align*} \mathbb{E}(\tilde{Y}(t,x_1,x_2)) &= \mathbb{E}(\frac{\sum_i K(x_{1i}, x_{2i}| x_1, x_2, \sigma)Y(t,x_{1i}, x_{2i})}{\sum_i K(x_{1i}, x_{2i}| x_1, x_2, \sigma)})\\ &= \frac{\sum_i K(x_{1i}, x_{2i}| x_1, x_2, \sigma)\mathbb{E}(Y(t,x_{1i}, x_{2i}))}{\sum_i K(x_{1i}, x_{2i}| x_1, x_2, \sigma)} \end{align*}\]

\[\mathbb{E}(\tilde{Y}(x_1,x_2)) = \frac{\sum_i K(x_{1i}, x_{2i}| x_1, x_2, \sigma)X\beta_{x_{1i}, x_{2i}}}{\sum_i K(x_{1i}, x_{2i}| x_1, x_2, \sigma)}\]

\[\therefore \mathbb{E}(\hat{\tilde{\beta}(x_1,x_2)}) = \frac{\sum_i K(x_{1i}, x_{2i}| x_1, x_2, \sigma)\beta_{x_{1i}, x_{2i}}}{\sum_i K(x_{1i}, x_{2i}| x_1, x_2, \sigma)}\]

2. Thin Plate Spline Regression (TPSR) for Beta

\[Y = XPB\Gamma + \epsilon, \ \ \epsilon \sim N(0,I)\]

where

  • \(Y = (Y_1' \ \ Y_2' \ \cdots \ \ Y_V')'\): \(VT \times 1\) vector

  • \(X = \begin{pmatrix} X_0 & 0 & \cdots & 0\\ 0 & X_0 & \cdots & 0\\ \vdots & \ddots & &0\\ 0 & 0 & \cdots & X_0 \end{pmatrix}\): \(VT \times VSk_{\beta}\) matrix

  • \(P =\) Permutation matrix: \(VSk_{\beta} \times VSk_{\beta}\) matrix

  • \(P\begin{pmatrix} \beta_{1,1}\\ \beta_{1,2}\\ \vdots\\ \beta_{Sk_{\beta},V-1}\\ \beta_{Sk_{\beta},V}\\ \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} \beta_{1,1}\\ \beta_{2,1}\\ \vdots\\ \beta_{Sk_{\beta}-1,V}\\ \beta_{Sk_{\beta},V}\\ \end{pmatrix}\)

  • \(B = \begin{pmatrix} B_1 & 0 & \cdots & 0\\ 0 & B_2 & \cdots & 0\\ \vdots & \ddots & &0\\ 0 & 0 & \cdots& B_{Sk_{\beta}} \end{pmatrix}\): \(VSk_{\beta} \times Sk_{\beta}k_{\gamma}\) matrix

  • \(\Gamma = (\gamma_1' , \cdots, \gamma_{Sk_{\beta}}')'\): \(Sk_{\beta}k_{\gamma} \times 1\) vector.

Then we can fit \(\Gamma\) using linear regression model.

\[\hat{\Gamma} = ((XPB)'(XPB))^{-1}(XPB)'Y\] Fitted spatial \(\beta\) will be expressed as below:

\[\begin{align*} \hat{\beta_S} &= \begin{pmatrix} \hat{\beta_1}\\ \hat{\beta_2}\\ \vdots \\ \hat{\beta_V}\\ \end{pmatrix} = PB\hat{\Gamma} \end{align*}\]
